article.headline: Montana State 78, Sacramento State 75
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- JaRon Jefferson had 22 points and five rebounds to lead Montana State over Sacramento State 78-75. Marvin Moss had 11 points and six assists, and Derrick Edmonds added 11 points and six rebounds for the Bobcats (10-8, 3-1 Big Sky), who ended the Hornets' seven-game winning streak at home. Clark Woods had 20 points, and Alex Bausley scored 14 for Sacramento State (13-6, 4-1). Tied at 39, Jefferson hit a three 3-point shots during a 14-4 run to give Montana State a 53-43 lead with 12:20 left in the second. The Bobcats were up by 14 points until Sacramento State staged a 14-2 run to tie the game at 68 after Bausley hit a layup with 3:13 to go. Montana State did not go away quietly. Woods' free throw put the Hornets up 73-72, but the Bobcats took over after Al Beye's dunk on the next possession at the 1:30 mark, and they held on for the victory. Sacramento State's Loren Leath missed a 3-point shot with four seconds left that could have sent the game into overtime. Five leads were exchanged before Sacramento State took control and led 30-23 after a layup by Justin Williams with 3:24 left in the first half. The Hornets were ahead 32-29 at halftime.
